Papers
------

A readable paper by the current leading team of Netflix Prize, ATT. Their idea
on Section 4.4 is what Tommi mentioned about boosting.

  http://portal.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1281206

Various statistics about the Netflix Prize.  Seems like methods using SVD
(singular value decomposition) performs well.

  http://www.netflixprize.com/assets/NetflixPrizeKDD_to_appear.pdf

SVM style matrix factorization for collaborative filtering. Refer to
this for details on how to classify into multiple, ordered classes
(1-5).

  http://people.csail.mit.edu/jrennie/papers/icml05-mmmf.pdf


Data Sets and Competitions
--------------------------

Netflix Prize.

  http://www.netflixprize.com/

KDD Cup is the first and the oldest data mining competition, and is an integral
part of the annual ACM SIGKDD International Conference on Knowledge Discovery
and Data Mining (KDD). This year's KDD Cup will be related to (but different
from) the current Netflix Prize competition. There will also be a workshop at
the KDD-2007 conference, where the participants of both the KDD Cup and the
current Netflix Prize competition will present their papers and exchange ideas.
We are looking forward to an interesting competition and your participation. We
particularly encourage the participation of students.

  http://www.cs.uic.edu/~liub/Netflix-KDD-Cup-2007.html

MovieLens data set.

  http://www.grouplens.org/node/73

